When compiling in gfx/skia, I get these 8 lines of warning-output:
{
gfx/skia/skia/src/gpu/gl/GrGLCaps.cpp:1705:9: warning: code will never be executed [-Wunreachable-code]
        GrGLint numFormats;
        ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
gfx/skia/skia/src/gpu/gl/GrGLCaps.cpp:1703:9: note: silence by adding parentheses to mark code as explicitly dead
    if (false) {
        ^
        /* DISABLES CODE */ ( )
1 warning generated. 
}

(The code is *intentionally* disabled, and we could tell the compiler that it's intentional [and suppress the warning] by adding an extra layer of parens around "false", as it suggests.  However, it looks like we don't take patches to our skia clone, as described at
 https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/gfx/skia/patches/README

So: until this is fixed upstream, I propose that we simply disable this build warning for skia (as we do for a number of other build warnings), to reduce the non-actionable buildspew.

